result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley A Baur was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • False Swearing, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.32(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Ashley A Baur in court with attorney Amy L. Menzel.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily but withholds accepting of the plea to allow defendant the opportunity to complete terms of Deferred Acceptance of Guilty Plea Agreement. Court reviews collateral consequences, possible penalties if defendant would be found guilty of the felony in the future. Court reviews DAGPA with defendant, approves and signs agreement. Upon successful completion of terms of agreement, State will, after 5 years, move to amend charge to Class A Misdemeanor False Swearing and ask Court to impose fine/costs which defendant will have already paid. Bond remains in effect.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for June 24, 2019 at 11:45 am.
